{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775853388478,"sessionID":"ses_286e3dfd6ffeQx7CUBHQTDRBo3","part":{"id":"prt_d791c396e001Hb6ZYPs19tuf45","messageID":"msg_d791c3136001bOMKBs1eBfaRry","sessionID":"ses_286e3dfd6ffeQx7CUBHQTDRBo3","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/testing/agentcube_tdd_manifest.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/testing/agentcube_tdd_manifest.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube 核心模块测试契约 (TDD Manifest)\n2: \n3: 本规范定义了系统各核心组件必须实现的最小测试集。未通过以下测试用例的实现将被判定为“跑偏”。\n4: \n5: ## 1. Workload Manager (Go) - 核心准入测试\n6: - **Func: `CreateSandbox`**\n7:     - **Test-WM-1**: 必须 Mock Kubernetes Client，验证 `sandbox` 资源被正确创建。\n8:     - **Test-WM-2**: 验证 Session 冲突处理（同名 Sandbox 冲突时返回 409 或恢复现有会话）。\n9:     - **Test-WM-3**: 验证 Pod 状态同步逻辑。模拟 Pod 变为 `Running` 状态，验证 API 返回正确的 `Endpoint`。\n10: - **Func: `DeleteSession`**\n11:     - **Test-WM-4**: 验证物理资源的清理。确保调用了 K8s Delete API 且 Redis 记录同步删除。\n12: \n13: ## 2. Router (Go) - 高并发与安全测试\n14: - **Middleware: `AuthMiddleware`**\n15:     - **Test-RT-1**: 构造非法 JWT，验证返回 `401 Unauthorized`。\n16:     - **Test-RT-2**: 构造过期 JWT，验证返回 `Token Expired`。\n17: - **Proxy Logic: `HandleProxy`**\n18:     - **Test-RT-3**: 模拟后端超时，验证 Proxy 正确处理 `Gateway Timeout` 且不崩溃。\n19:     - **Test-RT-4**: 验证 Header 透传（Host, X-Forwarded-For 等）。\n20: \n21: ## 3. Session Store (Go) - 强一致性测试\n22: - **Store Interface: `RedisStore` / `ValkeyStore`**\n23:     - **Test-ST-1**: 验证对象序列化与反序列化（SessionInfo -> JSON -> SessionInfo）。\n24:     - **Test-ST-2**: 并发写测试。模拟 100 个并发请求写入同一 Session，验证无 Data Race。\n25: \n26: ## 4. PicoD (Go) - 执行引擎隔离测试\n27: - **Executor: `RunCode`**\n28:     - **Test-PD-1**: 验证资源限制（如 OOM）。模拟大内存分配，验证进程被正确杀掉并返回错误。\n29:     - **Test-PD-2**: 验证 Stdout 分块读取。处理超过 1MB 的输出，验证无缓冲区溢出。\n30: \n31: ## 5. Python SDK & CLI - 兼容性与易用性测试\n32: - **Class: `CodeInterpreterClient`**\n33:     - **Test-SDK-1**: 验证所有 HTTP 状态码映射。404 -> `NotFoundError`, 429 -> `RateLimitError`。\n34:     - **Test-SDK-2**: 验证文件上传协议。构造二进制流，验证 Multipart 封装符合 Router 规范。\n35: - **CLI: `kubectl-agentcube`**\n36:     - **Test-CLI-1**: 验证 `run` 命令的参数解析。测试 `--image`, `--env` 等参数的正确合并。\n37: \n38: ## 物理指标要求\n39: 1.  **测试/代码行数比 (T/C Ratio)**: 必须 > 0.4 (即每 100 行代码至少 40 行测试)。\n40: 2.  **用例完整性**: 每个源文件（`*.go`, `*.py`）必须存在对应的 `*_test.go` 或 `test_*.py`。\n\n(End of file - total 40 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube 核心模块测试契约 (TDD Manifest)\n\n本规范定义了系统各核心组件必须实现的最小测试集。未通过以下测试用例的实现将被判定为“跑偏”。\n\n## 1. Workload Manager (Go) - 核心准入测试\n- **Func: `CreateSandbox`**\n    - **Test-WM-1**: 必须 Mock Kubernetes Client，验证 `sandbox` 资源被正确创建。\n    - **Test-WM-2**: 验证 Session 冲突处理（同名 Sandbox 冲突时返回 409 或恢复现有会话）。\n    - **Test-WM-3**: 验证 Pod 状态同步逻辑。模拟 Pod 变为 `Running` 状态，验证 API 返回正确的 `Endpoint`。\n- **Func: `DeleteSession`**\n    - **Test-WM-4**: 验证物理资源的清理。确保调用了 K8s Delete API 且 Redis 记录同步删除。\n\n## 2. Router (Go) - 高并发与安全测试\n- **Middleware: `AuthMiddleware`**\n    - **Test-RT-1**: 构造非法 JWT，验证返回 `401 Unauthorized`。\n    - **Test-RT-2**: 构造过期 JWT，验证返回 `Token Expired`。\n- **Proxy Logic: `HandleProxy`**\n    - **Test-RT-3**: 模拟后端超时，验证 Proxy 正确处理 `Gateway Timeout` 且不崩溃。\n    - **Test-RT-4**: 验证 Header 透传（Host, X-Forwarded-For 等）。\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/testing/agentcube_tdd_manifest.md","time":{"start":1775853388451,"end":1775853388476}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775853388491,"sessionID":"ses_286e3dfd6ffeQx7CUBHQTDRBo3","part":{"id":"prt_d791c3e04001Pf5mvTGwSIVsUk","messageID":"msg_d791c3136001bOMKBs1eBfaRry","sessionID":"ses_286e3dfd6ffeQx7CUBHQTDRBo3","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: /*\n2: Copyright 2026 The Volcano Authors.\n3: \n4: Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n5: you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n6: You may obtain a copy of the License at\n7: \n8:     http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n9: \n10: Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n11: distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n12: WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n13: See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n14: limitations under the License.\n15: */\n16: \n17: package controller\n18: \n19: import (\n20: \t\"context\"\n21: \t\"time\"\n22: \n23: \t\"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/reconcile\"\n24: )\n25: \n26: // Reconciler defines the interface for reconciliation.\n27: type Reconciler interface {\n28: \t// Reconcile performs reconciliation for the given request.\n29: \t// Returns a Result indicating whether to requeue and when.\n30: \tReconcile(ctx context.Context, req reconcile.Request) (reconcile.Result, error)\n31: }\n32: \n33: // ReconcileResult is a wrapper around controller-runtime's Result.\n34: type ReconcileResult struct {\n35: \t// Requeue tells the controller to requeue the resource.\n36: \tRequeue bool\n37: \n38: \t// RequeueAfter tells the controller to requeue the resource after the specified duration.\n39: \tRequeueAfter time.Duration\n40: }\n41: \n42: // Result returns a controller-runtime Result from a ReconcileResult.\n43: func (r ReconcileResult) Result() reconcile.Result {\n44: \treturn reconcile.Result{\n45: \t\tRequeue:      r.Requeue,\n46: \t\tRequeueAfter: r.RequeueAfter,\n47: \t}\n48: }\n49: \n50: // Requeue returns a ReconcileResult that requeues immediately.\n51: func Requeue() ReconcileResult {\n52: \treturn ReconcileResult{\n53: \t\tRequeue: true,\n54: \t}\n55: }\n56: \n57: // RequeueAfter returns a ReconcileResult that requeues after the specified duration.\n58: func RequeueAfter(duration time.Duration) ReconcileResult {\n59: \treturn ReconcileResult{\n60: \t\tRequeueAfter: duration,\n61: \t}\n62: }\n63: \n64: // RequeueWithDelay returns a ReconcileResult that requeues after the specified duration.\n65: // This is an alias for RequeueAfter.\n66: func RequeueWithDelay(duration time.Duration) ReconcileResult {\n67: \treturn RequeueAfter(duration)\n68: }\n69: \n70: // Done returns a ReconcileResult indicating reconciliation is complete.\n71: func Done() ReconcileResult {\n72: \treturn ReconcileResult{}\n73: }\n74: \n75: // RequeueError returns a ReconcileResult that requeues after a calculated delay based on error.\n76: func RequeueError(err error, baseDelay time.Duration, retryCount int) ReconcileResult {\n77: \tif err == nil {\n78: \t\treturn Done()\n79: \t}\n80: \n81: \t// Calculate exponential backoff\n82: \tdelay := CalculateBackoff(baseDelay, 1000*time.Second, retryCount)\n83: \n84: \treturn ReconcileResult{\n85: \t\tRequeueAfter: delay,\n86: \t}\n87: }\n88: \n89: // IsRequeue returns true if the result indicates a requeue.\n90: func IsRequeue(r ReconcileResult) bool {\n91: \treturn r.Requeue || r.RequeueAfter > 0\n92: }\n93: \n94: // IsImmediateRequeue returns true if the result indicates an immediate requeue.\n95: func IsImmediateRequeue(r ReconcileResult) bool {\n96: \treturn r.Requeue && r.RequeueAfter == 0\n97: }\n\n(End of file - total 97 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"/*\nCopyright 2026 The Volcano Authors.\n\nLicensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\nyou may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\nYou may obtain a copy of the License at\n\n    http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n\nUnless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\ndistributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\nWITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\nSee the License for the specific language governing permissions and\nlimitations under the License.\n*/\n\npackage controller\n\nimport (\n\t\"context\"","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler.go","time":{"start":1775853388454,"end":1775853388488}}}}
