t: validation catches invalid values (negative, zero)\n39: \n40: **Verification Command:**\n41: ```bash\n42: go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/... -v -run \"TestReconcilerConfig\"\n43: ```\n44: \n45: ---\n46: \n47: ## Task 3: Create Finalizer Constants and Helpers\n48: **Verifiable Output:** `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/finalizer.go` with finalizer utilities\n49: \n50: - [ ] Create `finalizer.go` file\n51: - [ ] Define constants:\n52:   - `AgentRuntimeFinalizer = \"agentruntime.agentcube.io/finalizer\"`\n53:   - `CodeInterpreterFinalizer = \"codeinterpreter.agentcube.io/finalizer\"`\n54: - [ ] Implement `HasFinalizer(obj metav1.Object, finalizer string) bool`\n55: - [ ] Implement `AddFinalizer(obj metav1.Object, finalizer string) bool`\n56:   - Returns true if finalizer was added (not already present)\n57: - [ ] Implement `RemoveFinalizer(obj metav1.Object, finalizer string) bool`\n58:   - Returns true if finalizer was removed (was present)\n59: - [ ] Write unit tests\n60:   - Verify test: HasFinalizer returns true when present\n61:   - Verify test: HasFinalizer returns false when absent\n62:   - Verify test: AddFinalizer adds only if not present\n63:   - Verify test: RemoveFinalizer removes only if present\n64:   - Verify test: RemoveFinalizer preserves other finalizers\n65: \n66: **Verification Command:**\n67: ```bash\n68: go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/... -v -run \"TestFinalizer\"\n69: ```\n70: \n71: ---\n72: \n73: ## Task 4: Create OwnerReference Helpers\n74: **Verifiable Output:** `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/ownerref.go` with OwnerReference utilities\n75: \n76: - [ ] Create `ownerref.go` file\n77: - [ ] Implement `NewOwnerReference(owner client.Object, scheme *runtime.Scheme) (*metav1.OwnerReference, error)`\n78:   - Sets `Controller: true`\n79:   - Sets `BlockOwnerDeletion: true`\n80:   - Extracts APIVersion and Kind from scheme\n81: - [ ] Implement `SetOwnerReference(obj metav1.Object, ownerRef *metav1.OwnerReference)`\n82: - [ ] Implement `HasOwnerReference(obj metav1.Object, ownerUID types.UID) bool`\n83: - [ ] Write unit tests\n84:   - Verify test: OwnerReference has correct fields\n85:   - Verify test: Controller and BlockOwnerDeletion are true\n86:   - Verify test: HasOwnerReference finds by UID\n87: \n88: **Verification Command:**\n89: ```bash\n90: go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/... -v -run \"TestOwnerReference\"\n91: ```\n92: \n93: ---\n94: \n95: ## Task 5: Create Condition Management Utilities\n96: **Verifiable Output:** `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/conditions.go` with condition helpers\n97: \n98: - [ ] Create `conditions.go` file\n99: - [ ] Implement `SetCondition(conditions *[]runtimev1alpha1.Condition, condition runtimev1alpha1.Condition) bool`\n100:   - Updates existing condition if type matches\n101:   - Appends new condition if type doesn't exist\n102:   - Updates LastTransitionTime only when status changes\n103:   - Returns true if condition was modified\n104: - [ ] Implement `GetCondition(conditions []runtimev1alpha1.Condition, conditionType runtimev1alpha1.ConditionType) *runtimev1alpha1.Condition`\n105: - [ ] Implement `RemoveCondition(conditions *[]runtimev1alpha1.Condition, conditionType runtimev1alpha1.ConditionType) bool`\n106: - [ ] Implement `IsConditionTrue(conditions []runtimev1alpha1.Condition, conditionType runtimev1alpha1.ConditionType) bool`\n107: - [ ] Write unit tests\n108:   - Verify test: SetCondition adds new condition\n109:   - Verify test: SetCondition updates existing with status change\n110:   - Verify test: LastTransitionTime updates only on status change\n111:   - Verify test: GetCondition returns correct condition\n112:   - Verify test: RemoveCondition removes only specified type\n113:   - Verify test: IsConditionTrue works correctly\n114: \n115: **Verification Command:**\n116: ```bash\n117: go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/... -v -run \"TestCondition\"\n118: ```\n119: \n120: ---\n121: \n122: ## Task 6: Create Metrics Definitions\n123: **Verifiable Output:** `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/metrics.go` with Prometheus metrics\n124: \n125: - [ ] Create `metrics.go` file\n126: - [ ] Define metrics:\n127:   - `reconcileLatency = prometheus.NewHistogramVec(...)` with labels: controller, result\n128:   - `reconcileTotal = prometheus.NewCounterVec(...)` with labels: controller, result\n129:   - `reconcileQueueDepth = prometheus.NewGaugeVec(...)` with label: controller\n130:   - `reconcileRetriesTotal = prometheus.NewCounterVec(...)` with label: controller\n131: - [ ] Implement `RecordReconcileLatency(controller string, duration time.Duration, success bool)`\n132: - [ ] Implement `RecordReconcile(controller string, success bool)`\n133: - [ ] Implement `SetQueueDepth(controller string, depth int)`\n134: - [ ] Implement `RecordRetry(controller string)`\n135: - [ ] Implement `RegisterMetrics(reg prometheus.Registerer)`\n136: - [ ] Write unit tests\n137:   - Verify test: metrics are registered without error\n138:   - Verify test: recording metrics doesn't panic\n139: \n140: **Verification Command:**\n141: ```bash\n142: go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/... -v -run \"TestMetrics\"\n143: ```\n144: \n145: ---\n146: \n147: ## Task 7: Create Rate Limiter Configuration\n148: **Verifiable Output:** `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/ratelimiter.go` with rate limiter setup\n149: \n150: - [ ] Create `ratelimiter.go` file\n151: - [ ] Implement `NewRateLimiter(baseDelay, maxDelay time.Duration) workqueue.RateLimiter`\n152:   - Uses `workqueue.NewItemExponentialFailureRateLimiter(baseDelay, maxDelay)`\n153: - [ ] Implement `NewControllerRateLimiter(config ReconcilerConfig) workqueue.RateLimiter`\n154:   - Creates rate limiter with config values\n155:   - Adds ±10% jitter to prevent thundering herd\n156: - [ ] Write unit tests\n157:   - Verify test: rate limiter is created with correct delays\n158:   - Verify test: backoff increases exponentially\n159:   - Verify test: backoff is capped at max delay\n160: \n161: **Verification Command:**\n162: ```bash\n163: go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/... -v -run \"TestRateLimiter\"\n164: ```\n165: \n166: ---\n167: \n168: ## Task 8: Create Base Reconciler Interface\n169: **Verifiable Output:** `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler.go` with base reconciler\n170: \n171: - [ ] Create `reconciler.go` file\n172: - [ ] Define `Reconciler` interface:\n173:   - `Reconcile(ctx context.Context, req reconcile.Request) (reconcile.Result, error)`\n174: - [ ] Define `ReconcileResult` struct (wrapper for controller-runtime result)\n175: - [ ] Implement `Requeue() ReconcileResult`\n176: - [ ] Implement `RequeueAfter(duration time.Duration) ReconcileResult`\n177: - [ ] Implement `Done() ReconcileResult`\n178: - [ ] Write unit tests\n179:   - Verify test: Requeue returns Requeue=true\n180:   - Verify test: RequeueAfter returns correct duration\n181:   - Verify test: Done returns empty result\n182: \n183: **Verification Command:**\n184: ```bash\n185: go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/... -v -run \"TestReconcileResult\"\n186: ```\n187: \n188: ---\n189: \n190: ## Task 9: Create Controller Manager Bootstrap\n191: **Verifiable Output:** `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/manager.go` with manager setup\n192: \n193: - [ ] Create `manager.go` file\n194: - [ ] Define `ControllerManager` struct with fields:\n195:   - `mgr ctrl.Manager`\n196:   - `config ReconcilerConfig`\n197:   - `started bool`\n198: - [ ] Implement `NewControllerManager(kubeconfig *rest.Config, config ReconcilerConfig) (*ControllerManager, error)`\n199:   - Creates controller-runtime manager\n200:   - Registers scheme with CRD types (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter)\n201:   - Sets up health probe endpoints\n202: - [ ] Write unit tests with envtest\n203:   - Verify test: manager is created successfully\n204:   - Verify test: scheme is registered with CRD types\n205: \n206: **Verification Command:**\n207: ```bash\n208: go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/... -v -run \"TestControllerManager\" -tags=integration\n209: ```\n210: \n211: ---\n212: \n213: ## Task 10: Create AgentRuntime Reconciler Structure\n214: **Verifiable Output:** `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/agentruntime_controller.go` with reconciler struct\n215: \n216: - [ ] Create `agentruntime_controller.go` file\n217: - [ ] Define `AgentRuntimeReconciler` struct with fields:\n218:   - `client client.Client`\n219:   - `scheme *runtime.Scheme`\n220:   - `config ReconcilerConfig`\n221:   - `recorder record.EventRecorder`\n222: - [ ] Implement `NewAgentRuntimeReconciler(client client.Client, scheme *runtime.Scheme, config ReconcilerConfig) *AgentRuntimeReconciler`\n223: - [ ] Implement `SetupWithManager(mgr ctrl.Manager) error`\n224:   - Uses `ctrl.NewControllerManagedBy(mgr)`\n225:   - For type `&runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{}`\n226:   - Owns Pods (for status updates)\n227:   - With event filter (skip status-only updates)\n228: - [ ] Write unit tests\n229:   - Verify test: reconciler is initialized correctly\n230:   - Verify test: SetupWithManager configures controller correctly\n231: \n232: **Verification Command:**\n233: ```bash\n234: go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/... -v -run \"TestAgentRuntimeReconcilerSetup\"\n235: ```\n236: \n237: ---\n238: \n239: ## Task 11: Implement AgentRuntime Reconcile - Fetch and Initial Setup\n240: **Verifiable Output:** AgentRuntime reconciler fetches resource and handles not found\n241: \n242: - [ ] Implement fetch logic in `Reconcile()` method:\n243:   - Fetch AgentRuntime by namespaced name\n244:   - Handle NotFound error (return Done, nil - object was deleted)\n245: - [ ] Implement initial status setup:\n246:   - If status.phase is empty, set to Pending\n247: - [ ] Add finalizer if not present\n248: - [ ] Write unit tests with fake client\n249:   - Verify test: returns Done when resource not found\n250:   - Verify test: sets phase to Pending on new resource\n251:   - Verify test: adds finalizer on first reconcile\n252: \n253: **Verification Command:**\n254: ```bash\n255: go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/... -v -run \"TestAgentRuntimeReconcileFetch\"\n256: ```\n257: \n258: ---\n259: \n260: ## Task 12: Implement AgentRuntime Sandbox Creation\n261: **Verifiable Output:** AgentRuntime reconciler creates sandbox Pod\n262: \n263: - [ ] Implement sandbox creation logic:\n264:   - Check if sandbox Pod exists (by OwnerReference)\n265:   - If not exists, create Pod from AgentRuntime spec\n266:   - Set OwnerReference on created Pod\n267:   - Add `SandboxCreated` condition\n268: - [ ] Implement `getOrCreateSandboxPod(ctx, agentRuntime) (*corev1.Pod, error)` helper\n269: - [ ] Write unit tests\n270:   - Verify test: creates Pod when none exists\n271:   - Verify test: reuses existing Pod when present\n272:   - Verify test: Pod has correct OwnerReference\n273:   - Verify test: SandboxCreated condition is set\n274: \n275: **Verification Command:**\n276: ```bash\n277: go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/... -v -run \"TestAgentRuntimeReconcileSandbox\"\n278: ```\n279: \n280: ---\n281: \n282: ## Task 13: Implement AgentRuntime Status Updates\n283: **Verifiable Output:** AgentRuntime status reflects sandbox state\n284: \n285: - [ ] Implement status update based on Pod state:\n286:   - Pod Pending → AgentRuntime Pending\n287:   - Pod Running → AgentRuntime Running (with PodIP, SandboxID, StartTime)\n288:   - Pod Failed → AgentRuntime Failed\n289: - [ ] Implement `updateAgentRuntimeStatus(ctx, agentRuntime, pod) error`\n290:   - Sets phase, conditions, and status fields\n291:   - Uses `client.Status().Update()`\n292: - [ ] Handle status update conflicts (retry up to 3 times)\n293: - [ ] Write unit tests\n294:   - Verify test: phase transitions from Pending to Running\n295:   - Verify test: PodIP is recorded in status\n296:   - Verify test: SandboxID (Pod UID) is recorded\n297:   - Verify test: Ready condition is set when Running\n298: \n299: **Verification Command:**\n300: ```bash\n301: go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/... -v -run \"TestAgentRuntimeReconcileStatus\"\n302: ```\n303: \n304: ---\n305: \n306: ## Task 14: Implement AgentRuntime Deletion Handling\n307: **Verifiable Output:** AgentRuntime finalizer handles cleanup\n308: \n309: - [ ] Implement deletion handling:\n310:   - Check if DeletionTimestamp is set\n311:   - If finalizer present, execute cleanup\n312:   - Delete associated sandbox Pod\n313:   - Delete associated Services/Ingress if any\n314:   - Remove finalizer after cleanup\n315: - [ ] Implement `handleAgentRuntimeDeletion(ctx, agentRuntime) (reconcile.Result, error)`\n316: - [ ] Write unit tests\n317:   - Verify test: cleanup runs when deletion timestamp set\n318:   - Verify test: Pod is deleted during cleanup\n319:   - Verify test: finalizer is removed after cleanup\n320:   - Verify test: resource deletion proceeds after finalizer removal\n321: \n322: **Verification Command:**\n323: ```bash\n324: go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/... -v -run \"TestAgentRuntimeReconcileDeletion\"\n325: ```\n326: \n327: ---\n328: \n329: ## Task 15: Implement AgentRuntime Spec Updates\n330: **Verifiable Output:** AgentRuntime handles spec changes\n331: \n332: - [ ] Implement spec change detection:\n333:   - Compare Generation with ObservedGeneration\n334:   - If different, handle as update\n335: - [ ] Implement update logic:\n336:   - Set phase to Pending during update\n337:   - Apply new spec to sandbox\n338:   - Update ObservedGeneration after successful reconcile\n339: - [ ] Implement `handleAgentRuntimeUpdate(ctx, agentRuntime) error`\n340: - [ ] Write unit tests\n341:   - Verify test: spec change triggers update handling\n342:   - Verify test: ObservedGeneration is updated after reconcile\n343:   - Verify test: phase transitions during update\n344: \n345: **Verification Command:**\n346: ```bash\n347: go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/... -v -run \"TestAgentRuntimeReconcileUpdate\"\n348: ```\n349: \n350: ---\n351: \n352: ## Task 16: Create CodeInterpreter Reconciler Structure\n353: **Verifiable Output:** `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/codeinterpreter_controller.go` with reconciler struct\n354: \n355: - [ ] Create `codeinterpreter_controller.go` file\n356: - [ ] Define `CodeInterpreterReconciler` struct with fields:\n357:   - `client client.Client`\n358:   - `scheme *runtime.Scheme`\n359:   - `config ReconcilerConfig`\n360:   - `recorder record.EventRecorder`\n361: - [ ] Implement `NewCodeInterpreterReconciler(client client.Client, scheme *runtime.Scheme, config ReconcilerConfig) *CodeInterpreterReconciler`\n362: - [ ] Implement `SetupWithManager(mgr ctrl.Manager) error`\n363:   - For type `&runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter{}`\n364:   - Owns Pods and Services\n365: - [ ] Write unit tests\n366:   - Verify test: reconciler is initialized correctly\n367:   - Verify test: SetupWithManager configures controller correctly\n368: \n369: **Verification Command:**\n370: ```bash\n371: go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/... -v -run \"TestCodeInterpreterReconcilerSetup\"\n372: ```\n373: \n374: ---\n375: \n376: ## Task 17: Implement CodeInterpreter Reconcile - Basic Flow\n377: **Verifiable Output:** CodeInterpreter reconciler handles CRUD operations\n378: \n379: - [ ] Implement fetch and not-found handling\n380: - [ ] Implement finalizer management (add on create)\n381: - [ ] Implement basic status setup\n382: - [ ] Write unit tests\n383:   - Verify test: returns Done when resource not found\n384:   - Verify test: adds finalizer on first reconcile\n385: \n386: **Verification Command:**\n387: ```bash\n388: go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/... -v -run \"TestCodeInterpreterReconcileBasic\"\n389: ```\n390: \n391: ---\n392: \n393: ## Task 18: Implement CodeInterpreter Sandbox Creation\n394: **Verifiable Output:** CodeInterpreter reconciler creates sandbox resources\n395: \n396: - [ ] Implement sandbox creation:\n397:   - Create Pod from `spec.template`\n398:   - Configure ports from `spec.ports`\n399:   - Set OwnerReference on all created resources\n400:   - Handle AuthMode=picod (inject PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY)\n401: - [ ] Implement warm pool support:\n402:   - If `spec.warmPoolSize > 0`, create SandboxClaim instead\n403: - [ ] Write unit tests\n404:   - Verify test: creates Pod with correct spec\n405:   - Verify test: configures ports correctly\n406:   - Verify test: injects auth env var for picod mode\n407:   - Verify test: creates SandboxClaim when warm pool enabled\n408: \n409: **Verification Command:**\n410: ```bash\n411: go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/... -v -run \"TestCodeInterpreterReconcileSandbox\"\n412: ```\n413: \n414: ---\n415: \n416: ## Task 19: Implement CodeInterpreter Status Updates\n417: **Verifiable Output:** CodeInterpreter status reflects readiness\n418: \n419: - [ ] Implement ready state detection:\n420:   - Monitor Pod readiness\n421:   - Set `status.ready=true` when ready\n422:   - Set conditions: SandboxReady, Ready\n423: - [ ] Implement status update method\n424: - [ ] Write unit tests\n425:   - Verify test: ready status set when pod passes checks\n426:   - Verify test: conditions are updated correctly\n427: \n428: **Verification Command:**\n429: ```bash\n430: go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/... -v -run \"TestCodeInterpreterReconcileStatus\"\n431: ```\n432: \n433: ---\n434: \n435: ## Task 20: Implement CodeInterpreter Deletion Handling\n436: **Verifiable Output:** CodeInterpreter finalizer handles cleanup\n437: \n438: - [ ] Implement deletion handling:\n439:   - Release warm pool sandboxes if applicable\n440:   - Delete SandboxClaim or Sandbox\n441:   - Clean up associated resources\n442:   - Remove finalizer\n443: - [ ] Write unit tests\n444:   - Verify test: warm pool sandboxes are released\n445:   - Verify test: finalizer cleanup succeeds\n446: \n447: **Verification Command:**\n448: ```bash\n449: go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/... -v -run \"TestCodeInterpreterReconcileDeletion\"\n450: ```\n451: \n452: ---\n453: \n454: ## Task 21: Create Watch Event Handlers\n455: **Verifiable Output:** `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/watch.go` with event handlers\n456: \n457: - [ ] Create `watch.go` file\n458: - [ ] Implement `mapPodToAgentRuntime(pod client.Object) []reconcile.Request`\n459:   - Maps Pod events to owning AgentRuntime\n460:   - Uses OwnerReference to find parent\n461: - [ ] Implement `mapPodToCodeInterpreter(pod client.Object) []reconcile.Request`\n462: - [ ] Implement `mapServiceToCodeInterpreter(svc client.Object) []reconcile.Request`\n463: - [ ] Write unit tests\n464:   - Verify test: pod event maps to correct AgentRuntime\n465:   - Verify test: pod without owner returns empty\n466:   - Verify test: service event maps to CodeInterpreter\n467: \n468: **Verification Command:**\n469: ```bash\n470: go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/... -v -run \"TestWatchMapper\"\n471: ```\n472: \n473: ---\n474: \n475: ## Task 22: Implement Error Classification and Retry Logic\n476: **Verifiable Output:** Errors are classified as retryable or non-retryable\n477: \n478: - [ ] Create `errors.go` file\n479: - [ ] Define `IsRetryableError(err error) bool` function\n480:   - Retryable: API server unavailable, network timeout, conflict\n481:   - Non-retryable: RBAC forbidden, invalid spec, not found\n482: - [ ] Implement `ClassifyError(err error) (retryable bool, reason string)`\n483: - [ ] Update reconcilers to use error classification\n484: - [ ] Write unit tests\n485:   - Verify test: API errors are classified correctly\n486:   - Verify test: timeout is retryable\n487:   - Verify test: forbidden is non-retryable\n488: \n489: **Verification Command:**\n490: ```bash\n491: go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/... -v -run \"TestErrorClassification\"\n492: ```\n493: \n494: ---\n495: \n496: ## Task 23: Implement Panic Recovery\n497: **Verifiable Output:** Reconcilers recover from panics gracefully\n498: \n499: - [ ] Implement panic recovery in reconcile loop\n500: - [ ] Log panic with stack trace\n501: - [ ] Update metrics with panic count\n502: - [ ] Return error to trigger retry\n503: - [ ] Ensure controller continues processing other resources\n504: - [ ] Write unit tests (may need to use defer/recover pattern)\n505:   - Verify test: panic is recovered\n506:   - Verify test: error is returned after panic\n507: \n508: **Verification Command:**\n509: ```bash\n510: go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/... -v -run \"TestPanicRecovery\"\n511: ```\n512: \n513: ---\n514: \n515: ## Task 24: Create Controller Command Entry Point\n516: **Verifiable Output:** `cmd/workload-manager/controller.go` with controller command\n517: \n518: - [ ] Create `cmd/workload-manager/` directory if not exists\n519: - [ ] Create `controller.go` file\n520: - [ ] Implement `NewControllerCommand() *cobra.Command`\n521:   - Flags for: kubeconfig, metrics-addr, probe-addr, concurrent-reconciles\n522:   - Initializes controller manager\n523:   - Registers both reconcilers\n524:   - Starts manager and blocks\n525: - [ ] Add graceful shutdown handling\n526: - [ ] Write unit tests for command flags\n527:   - Verify test: flags are parsed correctly\n528: \n529: **Verification Command:**\n530: ```bash\n531: go build ./cmd/workload-manager/... && echo \"Controller command builds successfully\"\n532: ```\n533: \n534: ---\n535: \n536: ## Task 25: Integrate with WorkloadManager Service Layer\n537: **Verifiable Output:** Reconcilers integrate with existing service layer\n538: \n539: - [ ] Update `AgentRuntimeReconciler` to accept `Store` interface\n540: - [ ] Update `CodeInterpreterReconciler` to accept `Store` interface\n541: - [ ] Implement status update propagation to Store\n542:   - When status changes, update Store entry\n543: - [ ] Implement read from Store where appropriate\n544: - [ ] Write integration tests\n545:   - Verify test: Store is updated on status change\n546:   - Verify test: reconciler reads from Store correctly\n547: \n548: **Verification Command:**\n549: ```bash\n550: go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/... -v -run \"TestStoreIntegration\" -tags=integration\n551: ```\n552: \n553: ---\n554: \n555: ## Task 26: Implement Structured Logging\n556: **Verifiable Output:** All reconciler operations have structured logging\n557: \n558: - [ ] Add logger initialization to reconcilers\n559: - [ ] Log reconciliation start with fields:\n560:   - controller, resource_name, resource_namespace\n561: - [ ] Log reconciliation completion with fields:\n562:   - duration_ms, result, requeue\n563: - [ ] Log errors with context:\n564:   - error message, retry count, resource details\n565: - [ ] Ensure all log lines use structured format (key=value pairs)\n566: - [ ] Write tests to verify log output format\n567:   - Verify test: log contains required fields\n568: \n569: **Verification Command:**\n570: ```bash\n571: go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/... -v -run \"TestLogging\"\n572: ```\n573: \n574: ---\n575: \n576: ## Task 27: AgentRuntime Reconciler Unit Tests - Full Coverage\n577: **Verifiable Output:** `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/agentruntime_controller_test.go` with comprehensive tests\n578: \n579: - [ ] Test scenarios:\n580:   - Create new AgentRuntime → Pod created\n581:   - Pod becomes Running → Status updated\n582:   - Pod fails → Status shows Failed\n583:   - Delete AgentRuntime → Cleanup executes\n584:   - Spec update → ObservedGeneration updated\n585:   - API server error → Retry triggered\n586:   - Status conflict → Retried successfully\n587: - [ ] Use fake client for isolation\n588: - [ ] Mock Pod status transitions\n589: - [ ] Achieve >= 80% coverage for reconciler\n590: \n591: **Verification Command:**\n592: ```bash\n593: go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/... -v -run \"TestAgentRuntimeReconciler\" -coverprofile=coverage.out\n594: go tool cover -func=coverage.out | grep agentruntime_controller\n595: ```\n596: \n597: ---\n598: \n599: ## Task 28: CodeInterpreter Reconciler Unit Tests - Full Coverage\n600: **Verifiable Output:** `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/codeinterpreter_controller_test.go` with comprehensive tests\n601: \n602: - [ ] Test scenarios:\n603:   - Create CodeInterpreter → Pod created\n604:   - AuthMode=picod → PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY injected\n605:   - WarmPoolSize > 0 → SandboxClaim created\n606:   - Pod ready → Status.ready=true\n607:   - Delete → Warm pool released\n608: - [ ] Use fake client for isolation\n609: - [ ] Achieve >= 80% coverage for reconciler\n610: \n611: **Verification Command:**\n612: ```bash\n613: go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/... -v -run \"TestCodeInterpreterReconciler\" -coverprofile=coverage.out\n614: go tool cover -func=coverage.out | grep codeinterpreter_controller\n615: ```\n616: \n617: ---\n618: \n619: ## Task 29: Create Controller Test Suite Setup\n620: **Verifiable Output:** `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/suite_test.go` with envtest setup\n621: \n622: - [ ] Create `suite_test.go` file\n623: - [ ] Implement envtest setup for integration tests\n624: - [ ] Configure CRD paths for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter\n625: - [ ] Implement shared setup/teardown for integration tests\n626: - [ ] Write basic integration test verifying:\n627:   - Manager starts successfully\n628:   - Controllers are registered\n629:   - CRD resources can be created\n630: \n631: **Verification Command:**\n632: ```bash\n633: go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/... -v -run \"TestSuite\" -tags=integration\n634: ```\n635: \n636: ---\n637: \n638: ## Task 30: Implement Integration Test - End-to-End Reconciliation\n639: **Verifiable Output:** End-to-end reconciliation flow works\n640: \n641: - [ ] Create integration test:\n642:   1. Create AgentRuntime CR\n643:   2. Verify reconciler creates Pod\n644:   3. Update Pod status to Running\n645:   4. Verify AgentRuntime status updated\n646:   5. Delete AgentRuntime\n647:   6. Verify cleanup completes\n648: - [ ] Run same test for CodeInterpreter\n649: - [ ] Verify metrics are recorded\n650: \n651: **Verification Command:**\n652: ```bash\n653: go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/... -v -run \"TestEndToEndReconciliation\" -tags=integration\n654: ```\n655: \n656: ---\n657: \n658: ## Task 31: Implement Integration Test - Concurrent Reconciliations\n659: **Verifiable Output:** Multiple reconciliations work concurrently\n660: \n661: - [ ] Create integration test:\n662:   - Create 10 AgentRuntimes simultaneously\n663:   - Verify all are reconciled\n664:   - Verify no race conditions\n665:   - Verify correct status for all\n666: - [ ] Use `-race` flag to detect data races\n667: \n668: **Verification Command:**\n669: ```bash\n670: go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/... -race -v -run \"TestConcurrentReconciliation\" -tags=integration\n671: ```\n672: \n673: ---\n674: \n675: ## Task 32: Implement Integration Test - Rate Limiting and Backoff\n676: **Verifiable Output:** Rate limiting and backoff work correctly\n677: \n678: - [ ] Create integration test:\n679:   - Trigger reconciliation failures\n680:   - Verify exponential backoff delays\n681:   - Verify retry counter increments\n682:   - Verify success resets backoff\n683: - [ ] Verify max retry limit is respected\n684: \n685: **Verification Command:**\n686: ```bash\n687: go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/... -v -run \"TestRateLimiting\" -tags=integration\n688: ```\n689: \n690: ---\n691: \n692: ## Task 33: Implement Integration Test - Watch Reconnection\n693: **Verifiable Output:** Watch reconnects on connection loss\n694: \n695: - [ ] Create integration test:\n696:   - Simulate watch connection drop\n697:   - Verify reconnection attempts\n698:   - Verify no events lost after reconnection\n699: - [ ] May require mocking API server behavior\n700: \n701: **Verification Command:**\n702: ```bash\n703: go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/... -v -run \"TestWatchReconnection\" -tags=integration\n704: ```\n705: \n706: ---\n707: \n708: ## Task 34: Verify Metrics Endpoint\n709: **Verifiable Output:** Metrics are exposed correctly\n710: \n711: - [ ] Verify metrics are registered\n712: - [ ] Test metrics endpoint returns data\n713: - [ ] Verify metric labels are correct:\n714:   - controller=agentruntime/codeinterpreter\n715:   - result=success/error\n716: - [ ] Test queue depth metric updates\n717: \n718: **Verification Command:**\n719: ```bash\n720: curl -s http://localhost:8080/metrics | grep reconcile\n721: go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/... -v -run \"TestMetricsEndpoint\" -tags=integration\n722: ```\n723: \n724: ---\n725: \n726: ## Task 35: Verify Health Probe Endpoints\n727: **Verifiable Output:** Health probes work correctly\n728: \n729: - [ ] Verify `/readyz` endpoint returns 200 when ready\n730: - [ ] Verify `/readyz` returns non-200 when not ready\n731: - [ ] Verify `/livez` endpoint returns 200 when healthy\n732: - [ ] Test probes during startup and shutdown\n733: \n734: **Verification Command:**\n735: ```bash\n736: curl -s http://localhost:8081/readyz\n737: go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/... -v -run \"TestHealthProbes\" -tags=integration\n738: ```\n739: \n740: ---\n741: \n742: ## Task 36: Document Controller Architecture\n743: **Verifiable Output:** Controller architecture documented\n744: \n745: - [ ] Update `design.md` with detailed component descriptions\n746: - [ ] Document data flow for reconciliation\n747: - [ ] Document error handling strategy\n748: - [ ] Document integration points with service layer\n749: \n750: **Verification Command:**\n751: ```bash\n752: cat changes/AR-007/design.md | grep -A 5 \"Components\"\n753: ```\n754: \n755: ---\n756: \n757: ## Task 37: Final Compilation Check\n758: **Verifiable Output:** Clean build with no errors\n759: \n760: - [ ] Run `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/...`\n761: - [ ] Run `go build ./cmd/workload-manager/...`\n762: - [ ] Run `go vet ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/...`\n763: - [ ] Fix any vet warnings\n764: \n765: **Verification Command:**\n766: ```bash\n767: go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/... && \\\n768: go build ./cmd/workload-manager/... && \\\n769: go vet ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/... && \\\n770: echo \"Build and vet passed\"\n771: ```\n772: \n773: ---\n774: \n775: ## Task 38: Verify Test Coverage\n776: **Verifiable Output:** Coverage meets targets\n777: \n778: - [ ] Run tests with coverage: `go test -coverprofile=coverage.out ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/...`\n779: - [ ] Verify controller package coverage >= 80%\n780: - [ ] Verify reconciler coverage >= 80%\n781: - [ ] Generate coverage report\n782: \n783: **Verification Command:**\n784: ```bash\n785: go test -race -v -coverprofile=coverage.out -coverpkg=./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/... ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller/...\n786: go tool cover -func=coverage.out | awk 'END {print \"Total coverage:\", $3}'\n787: ```\n788: \n789: ---\n790: \n791: ## Task 39: Verify Compatibility with AR-003/AR-004/AR-005/AR-006\n792: **Verifiable Output:** Compatible with existing ARs\n793: \n794: - [ ] Verify CRD types from AR-003 are usable\n795: - [ ] Verify HTTP framework from AR-004 works alongside controller\n796: - [ ] Verify AR-005 sandbox creation works with controller\n797: - [ ] Verify AR-006 sandbox deletion works with controller\n798: - [ ] Check for any circular dependencies\n799: \n800: **Verification Command:**\n801: ```bash\n802: go build ./... && echo \"All packages compile together\"\n803: ```\n804: \n805: ---\n806: \n807: ## Task 40: Integration with Main Application\n808: **Verifiable Output:** Controller integrates with main workload-manager binary\n809: \n810: - [ ] Update main.go to support controller mode\n811: - [ ] Verify controller can run alongside HTTP server\n812: - [ ] Verify shared resources (Store, Client) work correctly\n813: - [ ] Test full application startup\n814: \n815: **Verification Command:**\n816: ```bash\n817: go build -o /tmp/workload-manager ./cmd/workload-manager/... && /tmp/workload-manager --help | grep controller\n818: ```\n819: \n820: ---\n821: \n822: ## Completion Criteria\n823: \n824: - [ ] All tasks 1-40 completed\n825: - [ ] All unit tests pass\n826: - [ ] All integration tests pass (with -tags=integration)\n827: - [ ] Controller package coverage >= 80%\n828: - [ ] Reconciler coverage >= 80%\n829: - [ ] No compilation errors\n830: - [ ] No vet warnings\n831: - [ ] No race conditions detected (go test -race)\n832: - [ ] Metrics are exposed correctly\n833: - [ ] Health probes work correctly\n834: - [ ] Documentation complete\n835: - [ ] Compatible with AR-003 through AR-006\n836: - [ ] Controller can run standalone or alongside HTTP server\n837: \n838: ---\n839: \n840: ## Summary\n841: \n842: - **Total Tasks:** 40\n843: - **Estimated Total Hours:** 80-100\n844: - **Status:** Not Started\n845: \n\n(End of file - total 845 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-007 Tasks: K8s Reconciler 控制器\n\n> **Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n> **Language:** Go  \n> **Size:** L  \n> **Stage:** ST-3 completed\n\n---\n\n## Task 1: Create Controller Directory Structure\n**Verifiable Output:** Directory structure created for controller package\n\n- [ ] Create directory `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/`\n- [ ] Create directory `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/internal/`\n- [ ] Verify directory structure exists\n\n**Verification Command:**\n```bash\nls -la pkg/workloadmanager/controller/\n```","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-007/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775853408833,"end":1775853408862}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775853408869,"sessionID":"ses_286e3dfd6ffeQx7CUBHQTDRBo3","part":{"id":"prt_d791c8009001q0pCVwbYhOcyx3","messageID":"msg_d791c6724001332brpKN7Ig0AR","sessionID":"ses_286e3dfd6ffeQx7CUBHQTDRBo3","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:12","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-007/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-007/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-007 — K8s Reconciler 控制器\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **AR ID:** AR-007  \n6: **Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n7: **Language:** Go  \n8: **Size:** L  \n9: \n10: Implement the Kubernetes Reconciler Controller for the WorkloadManager using controller-runtime. The controller watches AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRs, reconciles their desired state with actual cluster state, manages sandbox lifecycle transitions, and provides event-driven reconciliation with exponential backoff, finalizers, and proper status condition management.\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Requirements\n15: \n16: ### Requirement: Controller Manager Bootstrap\n17: \n18: The system SHALL provide a controller manager that initializes and manages reconciler controllers.\n19: \n20: #### Scenario: Start controller manager with reconcilers\n21: - **GIVEN** a valid Kubernetes configuration and WorkloadManager configuration\n22: - **WHEN** the operator calls `controllerManager.Start(ctx)`\n23: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n24:   1. Create a new controller-runtime manager with the provided configuration\n25:   2. Register the AgentRuntimeReconciler with the manager\n26:   3. Register the CodeInterpreterReconciler with the manager\n27:   4. Start all controllers in separate goroutines\n28:   5. Block until context cancellation or error\n29: \n30: #### Scenario: Controller manager uses in-cluster config\n31: - **GIVEN** the WorkloadManager is running inside a Kubernetes pod\n32: - **WHEN** the controller manager initializes\n33: - **THEN** it SHALL use `ctrl.GetConfigOrDie()` to get in-cluster configuration\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Controller manager uses kubeconfig\n36: - **GIVEN** a valid kubeconfig file at `~/.kube/config` when running outside the cluster\n37: - **WHEN** the controller manager initializes\n38: - **THEN** it SHALL use the kubeconfig to connect to the Kubernetes API server\n39: \n40: #### Scenario: Controller manager shuts down gracefully\n41: - **GIVEN** the controller manager is running with active reconciliations\n42: - **WHEN** the context is cancelled\n43: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n44:   1. Stop accepting new reconciliation requests\n45:   2. Wait for in-progress reconciliations to complete (up to graceful timeout)\n46:   3. Stop all watches and release resources\n47:   4. Return without error\n48: \n49: #### Scenario: Controller manager health check\n50: - **GIVEN** the controller manager is running\n51: - **WHEN** the `/readyz` endpoint is called\n52: - **THEN** it SHALL return ready only when all controllers are started and caches are synced\n53: \n54: ---\n55: \n56: ### Requirement: AgentRuntime Reconciler\n57: \n58: The system SHALL implement a reconciler for AgentRuntime resources.\n59: \n60: #### Scenario: Reconcile new AgentRuntime creation\n61: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime named `new-runtime` is created in namespace `default`\n62: - **WHEN** the reconciler receives the creation event\n63: - **THEN** it SHALL:\n64:   1. Fetch the AgentRuntime object from the API server\n65:   2. Set initial status phase to `Pending`\n66:   3. Add finalizer `agentruntime.agentcube.io/finalizer` if not present\n67:   4. Create the underlying sandbox Pod\n68:   5. Set OwnerReference on the Pod pointing to the AgentRuntime\n69:   6. Update status with `SandboxCreated` condition set to `True`\n70:   7. Requeue after 5 seconds to check sandbox status\n71: \n72: #### Scenario: Reconcile AgentRuntime sandbox running\n73: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with a sandbox Pod in `Running` phase\n74: - **WHEN** the reconciler processes the resource\n75: - **THEN** it SHALL:\n76:   1. Check the Pod status via API server\n77:   2. Update AgentRuntime status phase to `Running`\n78:   3. Set `SandboxReady` condition to `True`\n79:   4. Set `Ready` condition to `True`\n80:   5. Update `Status.PodIP` with the pod's IP address\n81:   6. Update `Status.SandboxID` with the pod's UID\n82:   7. Update `Status.StartTime` with the pod's start time\n83: \n84: #### Scenario: Reconcile AgentRuntime sandbox failure\n85: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with a sandbox Pod in `Failed` phase\n86: - **WHEN** the reconciler processes the resource\n87: - **THEN** it SHALL:\n88:   1. Update status phase to `Failed`\n89:   2. Set `Failed` condition to `True` with reason and message\n90:   3. Set `Ready` condition to `False`\n91:   4. Record the failure reason in `Status.Reason`\n92:   5. Record error message in `Status.Message`\n93: \n94: #### Scenario: Reconcile AgentRuntime spec update\n95: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with generation `2` and observedGeneration `1`\n96: - **WHEN** the reconciler processes the resource\n97: - **THEN** it SHALL:\n98:   1. Detect the spec change (generation != observedGeneration)\n99:   2. Set phase to `Pending` during update\n100:   3. Apply the new spec to the sandbox resources\n101:   4. Update `Status.ObservedGeneration` to match generation\n102:   5. Requeue to monitor the update progress\n103: \n104: #### Scenario: Reconcile AgentRuntime with finalizer on deletion\n105: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with deletion timestamp set and finalizer present\n106: - **WHEN** the reconciler processes the deletion\n107: - **THEN** it SHALL:\n108:   1. Set phase to `Pending` (terminating state)\n109:   2. Delete the associated sandbox Pod\n110:   3. Delete any associated Services or Ingress resources\n111:   4. Remove the finalizer from the AgentRuntime\n112:   5. Allow Kubernetes to garbage collect the AgentRuntime\n113: \n114: #### Scenario: Handle AgentRuntime not found\n115: - **GIVEN** a reconciliation request for an AgentRuntime that no longer exists\n116: - **WHEN** the reconciler fetches the resource\n117: - **THEN** it SHALL return without error (object was deleted)\n118: \n119: ---\n120: \n121: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreter Reconciler\n122: \n123: The system SHALL implement a reconciler for CodeInterpreter resources.\n124: \n125: #### Scenario: Reconcile new CodeInterpreter creation\n126: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter named `new-interpreter` is created in namespace `default`\n127: - **WHEN** the reconciler receives the creation event\n128: - **THEN** it SHALL:\n129:   1. Fetch the CodeInterpreter object from the API server\n130:   2. Set initial `Ready` status to `false`\n131:   3. Add finalizer `codeinterpreter.agentcube.io/finalizer` if not present\n132:   4. Create the sandbox Pod from `spec.template`\n133:   5. Configure ports from `spec.ports`\n134:   6. Set OwnerReference on created resources\n135:   7. Add `SandboxCreated` condition with status `True`\n136: \n137: #### Scenario: Reconcile CodeInterpreter with warm pool\n138: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `spec.warmPoolSize > 0`\n139: - **WHEN** the reconciler processes the resource\n140: - **THEN** it SHALL:\n141:   1. Create a SandboxClaim instead of direct Sandbox\n142:   2. Set `SandboxClaimCreated` condition\n143:   3. Monitor the SandboxClaim status\n144:   4. Update CodeInterpreter status when sandbox is assigned\n145: \n146: #### Scenario: Reconcile CodeInterpreter ready state\n147: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with a running sandbox Pod\n148: - **WHEN** the pod passes readiness checks\n149: - **THEN** it SHALL:\n150:   1. Set `Status.Ready` to `true`\n151:   2. Set `SandboxReady` condition to `True`\n152:   3. Set `Ready` condition to `True`\n153:   4. Record the ready transition timestamp\n154: \n155: #### Scenario: Reconcile CodeInterpreter auth configuration\n156: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `spec.authMode=picod`\n157: - **WHEN** the reconciler creates the sandbox\n158: - **THEN** it SHALL:\n159:   1. Inject `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` environment variable\n160:   2. Configure authentication sidecar if required\n161:   3. Set appropriate labels for auth routing\n162: \n163: #### Scenario: Reconcile CodeInterpreter deletion\n164: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with deletion timestamp set\n165: - **WHEN** the reconciler processes the deletion\n166: - **THEN** it SHALL:\n167:   1. Release warm pool sandboxes if applicable\n168:   2. Delete the SandboxClaim or Sandbox\n169:   3. Clean up associated resources\n170:   4. Remove the finalizer\n171: \n172: ---\n173: \n174: ### Requirement: Event-Driven Watch and Reconciliation\n175: \n176: The system SHALL use informers to watch for resource changes and trigger reconciliation.\n177: \n178: #### Scenario: Watch AgentRuntime events\n179: - **GIVEN** the AgentRuntime reconciler is running\n180: - **WHEN** an AgentRuntime is created, updated, or deleted\n181: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n182:   1. Receive the event from the API server watch stream\n183:   2. Map the event to a reconciliation request\n184:   3. Add the request to the work queue\n185:   4. Wake up a worker to process the request\n186: \n187: #### Scenario: Watch CodeInterpreter events\n188: - **GIVEN** the CodeInterpreter reconciler is running\n189: - **WHEN** a CodeInterpreter resource changes\n190: - **THEN** the system SHALL enqueue a reconciliation request for that resource\n191: \n192: #### Scenario: Watch owned Pod events\n193: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime has created a sandbox Pod\n194: - **WHEN** the Pod status changes (e.g., transitions to Running)\n195: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n196:   1. Map the Pod event to its owning AgentRuntime\n197:   2. Enqueue a reconciliation request for the AgentRuntime\n198:   3. Trigger status update based on Pod state\n199: \n200: #### Scenario: Watch owned Service events\n201: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter has created a Service\n202: - **WHEN** the Service endpoints are updated\n203: - **THEN** the system SHALL enqueue a reconciliation for the owning CodeInterpreter\n204: \n205: #### Scenario: Handle watch reconnection\n206: - **GIVEN** the API server watch connection is lost\n207: - **WHEN** the connection drops\n208: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n209:   1. Log the disconnection event\n210:   2. Attempt to reconnect with exponential backoff\n211:   3. Resync the cache on reconnection\n212:   4. Continue processing without data loss\n213: \n214: ---\n215: \n216: ### Requirement: Reconcile Queue with Rate Limiting\n217: \n218: The system SHALL implement a work queue with rate limiting for reconciliation requests.\n219: \n220: #### Scenario: Add request to queue\n221: - **GIVEN** a reconciliation request for AgentRuntime `test-runtime`\n222: - **WHEN** the request is enqueued\n223: - **THEN** the system SHALL add it to the work queue with the resource namespace and name\n224: \n225: #### Scenario: Process request from queue\n226: - **GIVEN** a worker is available and a request is in the queue\n227: - **WHEN** the worker dequeues the request\n228: - **THEN** it SHALL call the appropriate reconciler's `Reconcile()` method\n229: \n230: #### Scenario: Rate limit failed reconciliations\n231: - **GIVEN** a reconciliation fails with a retryable error\n232: - **WHEN** the error is returned\n233: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n234:   1. Increment the retry counter for the resource\n235:   2. Calculate backoff delay using exponential backoff (base 5ms, max 1000s)\n236:   3. Re-add the request to the queue with the calculated delay\n237:   4. Not block other reconciliations\n238: \n239: #### Scenario: Max retries exceeded\n240: - **GIVEN** a resource has failed reconciliation 5 times\n241: - **WHEN** the max retry limit is reached\n242: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n243:   1. Drop the request from the queue\n244:   2. Update the resource status with `Failed` condition\n245:   3. Record the permanent failure in status\n246:   4. Log the error for operator investigation\n247: \n248: #### Scenario: Successful reconciliation resets rate limit\n249: - **GIVEN** a resource that previously failed reconciliation\n250: - **WHEN** the reconciliation succeeds\n251: - **THEN** the system SHALL reset the retry counter for that resource to zero\n252: \n253: #### Scenario: Concurrent workers process queue\n254: - **GIVEN** the controller is configured with 3 concurrent workers\n255: - **WHEN** multiple requests are in the queue\n256: - **THEN** the system SHALL process up to 3 reconciliations concurrently\n257: \n258: ---\n259: \n260: ### Requirement: Exponential Backoff for Failures\n261: \n262: The system SHALL implement exponential backoff for transient failures.\n263: \n264: #### Scenario: Calculate backoff delay\n265: - **GIVEN** a resource has failed reconciliation `n` times\n266: - **WHEN** calculating the next retry delay\n267: - **THEN** the system SHALL use the formula: `min(base * 2^n, max)` where base=5ms, max=1000s\n268: \n269: #### Scenario: Apply jitter to backoff\n270: - **GIVEN** a calculated backoff of 10 seconds\n271: - **WHEN** scheduling the retry\n272: - **THEN** the system SHALL add ±10% jitter to prevent thundering herd\n273: \n274: #### Scenario: Reset backoff on success\n275: - **GIVEN** a resource with accumulated backoff delay\n276: - **WHEN** reconciliation succeeds\n277: - **THEN** the system SHALL reset the backoff to the base value\n278: \n279: #### Scenario: Skip backoff for non-retryable errors\n280: - **GIVEN** a reconciliation fails with a non-retryable error (e.g., invalid spec)\n281: - **WHEN** the error is returned\n282: - **THEN** the system SHALL not retry and update status with permanent failure\n283: \n284: ---\n285: \n286: ### Requirement: Finalizer Handling\n287: \n288: The system SHALL implement finalizers for graceful resource cleanup.\n289: \n290: #### Scenario: Add finalizer on creation\n291: - **GIVEN** a new AgentRuntime resource without finalizers\n292: - **WHEN** the reconciler first processes the resource\n293: - **THEN** it SHALL add the finalizer `agentruntime.agentcube.io/finalizer`\n294: \n295: #### Scenario: Execute finalizer on deletion\n296: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with deletion timestamp and finalizer present\n297: - **WHEN** the reconciler processes the resource\n298: - **THEN** it SHALL:\n299:   1. Check if deletion timestamp is set\n300:   2. Execute cleanup logic (delete pods, services)\n301:   3. Remove the finalizer from the resource\n302:   4. Return to allow Kubernetes deletion\n303: \n304: #### Scenario: Multiple finalizers handling\n305: - **GIVEN** a resource with multiple finalizers including the controller's finalizer\n306: - **WHEN** processing deletion\n307: - **THEN** the system SHALL only remove its own finalizer and preserve others\n308: \n309: #### Scenario: Finalizer cleanup failure\n310: - **GIVEN** cleanup fails during finalizer execution (e.g., API server error)\n311: - **WHEN** the error occurs\n312: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n313:   1. Not remove the finalizer\n314:   2. Return the error to trigger retry\n315:   3. Keep the resource in terminating state\n316: \n317: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter finalizer\n318: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter resource\n319: - **WHEN** processed by the reconciler\n320: - **THEN** it SHALL use finalizer `codeinterpreter.agentcube.io/finalizer`\n321: \n322: ---\n323: \n324: ### Requirement: Status Updates and Condition Management\n325: \n326: The system SHALL properly manage resource status and conditions.\n327: \n328: #### Scenario: Update AgentRuntime status\n329: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime reconciliation determines new state\n330: - **WHEN** updating status\n331: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n332:   1. Use the status subresource update (`UpdateStatus`)\n333:   2. Set appropriate phase (Pending, Running, Succeeded, Failed, Unknown)\n334:   3. Update conditions with proper transition timestamps\n335:   4. Preserve existing conditions not being modified\n336: \n337: #### Scenario: Add new condition\n338: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime without a `SandboxCreated` condition\n339: - **WHEN** the sandbox is created\n340: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n341:   1. Append a new `AgentRuntimeCondition` to the conditions array\n342:   2. Set `Type`, `Status`, `LastTransitionTime`, `Reason`, and `Message`\n343:   3. Use strategic merge patch to avoid conflicts\n344: \n345: #### Scenario: Update existing condition\n346: - **GIVEN** an existing condition with status `False`\n347: - **WHEN** the condition status changes to `True`\n348: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n349:   1. Update the `Status` field\n350:   2. Update `LastTransitionTime` to now\n351:   3. Update `Reason` and `Message` if provided\n352: \n353: #### Scenario: Observed generation tracking\n354: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with `metadata.generation=5`\n355: - **WHEN** spec reconciliation completes\n356: - **THEN** the system SHALL set `status.observedGeneration=5`\n357: \n358: #### Scenario: Handle status update conflict\n359: - **GIVEN** a status update fails with conflict error\n360: - **WHEN** the error occurs\n361: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n362:   1. Fetch the latest resource version\n363:   2. Re-apply the status changes\n364:   3. Retry the update (up to 3 times)\n365: \n366: #### Scenario: Update CodeInterpreter ready status\n367: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with running sandbox\n368: - **WHEN** all readiness checks pass\n369: - **THEN** the system SHALL set `status.ready=true` and update conditions\n370: \n371: ---\n372: \n373: ### Requirement: OwnerReference Management\n374: \n375: The system SHALL set OwnerReferences on created resources for garbage collection.\n376: \n377: #### Scenario: Set OwnerReference on Pod\n378: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime creates a sandbox Pod\n379: - **WHEN** creating the Pod\n380: - **THEN** the system SHALL set:\n381:   ```yaml\n382:   ownerReferences:\n383:   - apiVersion: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\n384:     kind: AgentRuntime\n385:     name: <agentruntime-name>\n386:     uid: <agentruntime-uid>\n387:     controller: true\n388:     blockOwnerDeletion: true\n389:   ```\n390: \n391: #### Scenario: Set OwnerReference on Service\n392: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter creates a Service\n393: - **WHEN** creating the Service\n394: - **THEN** the system SHALL set OwnerReference pointing to the CodeInterpreter\n395: \n396: #### Scenario: Set OwnerReference on ConfigMap\n397: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter creates a ConfigMap for configuration\n398: - **WHEN** creating the ConfigMap\n399: - **THEN** the system SHALL set OwnerReference for automatic cleanup\n400: \n401: #### Scenario: Cascade deletion with OwnerReference\n402: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with OwnerReference-set Pods\n403: - **WHEN** the AgentRuntime is deleted\n404: - **THEN** Kubernetes SHALL automatically garbage collect the owned Pods\n405: \n406: ---\n407: \n408: ### Requirement: Integration with WorkloadManager Service Layer\n409: \n410: The system SHALL integrate with the existing WorkloadManager HTTP service.\n411: \n412: #### Scenario: Reconciler updates Store via service layer\n413: - **GIVEN** a reconciliation updates sandbox status\n414: - **WHEN** status changes from `Pending` to `Running`\n415: - **THEN** the system SHALL call the service layer to update the Store entry\n416: \n417: #### Scenario: Service layer triggers reconciliation\n418: - **GIVEN** an HTTP request modifies an AgentRuntime\n419: - **WHEN** the modification is applied via Kubernetes API\n420: - **THEN** the watch SHALL trigger reconciliation\n421: \n422: #### Scenario: Reconciler reads from informer cache\n423: - **GIVEN** the reconciler needs to list related resources\n424: - **WHEN** querying resources\n425: - **THEN** it SHALL use the informer cache for efficiency, falling back to API server on cache miss\n426: \n427: #### Scenario: Shared informer factory\n428: - **GIVEN** both reconcilers and HTTP handlers need resource information\n429: - **WHEN** initializing the system\n430: - **THEN** the system SHALL use a shared informer factory to avoid duplicate watches\n431: \n432: ---\n433: \n434: ### Requirement: Metrics and Observability\n435: \n436: The system SHALL expose metrics for reconciliation operations.\n437: \n438: #### Scenario: Expose reconcile latency metric\n439: - **GIVEN** a reconciliation completes\n440: - **WHEN** metrics endpoint is scraped\n441: - **THEN** the system SHALL expose `reconcile_latency_seconds` histogram with labels:\n442:   - `controller` (agentruntime/codeinterpreter)\n443:   - `result` (success/error)\n444: \n445: #### Scenario: Expose reconcile count metric\n446: - **GIVEN** reconciliations are being processed\n447: - **WHEN** metrics are collected\n448: - **THEN** the system SHALL expose `reconcile_total` counter with labels:\n449:   - `controller`\n450:   - `result`\n451: \n452: #### Scenario: Expose queue depth metric\n453: - **GIVEN** the work queue has pending items\n454: - **WHEN** metrics are collected\n455: - **THEN** the system SHALL expose `reconcile_queue_depth` gauge per controller\n456: \n457: #### Scenario: Expose retry count metric\n458: - **GIVEN** resources are being retried\n459: - **WHEN** metrics are collected\n460: - **THEN** the system SHALL expose `reconcile_retries_total` counter\n461: \n462: #### Scenario: Structured logging for reconciliation\n463: - **GIVEN** a reconciliation is processed\n464: - **WHEN** logging\n465: - **THEN** the system SHALL include fields:\n466:   - `controller`\n467:   - `resource_name`\n468:   - `resource_namespace`\n469:   - `operation` (create/update/delete)\n470:   - `duration_ms`\n471:   - `result`\n472: \n473: #### Scenario: Log reconciliation errors\n474: - **GIVEN** a reconciliation fails\n475: - **WHEN** logging the error\n476: - **THEN** the system SHALL include:\n477:   - Error message\n478:   - Stack trace (if available)\n479:   - Resource details\n480:   - Retry count\n481: \n482: ---\n483: \n484: ### Requirement: Error Handling and Recovery\n485: \n486: The system SHALL handle errors gracefully and recover when possible.\n487: \n488: #### Scenario: Handle API server unavailable\n489: - **GIVEN** the Kubernetes API server is temporarily unavailable\n490: - **WHEN** the reconciler tries to fetch/update a resource\n491: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n492:   1. Log the error\n493:   2. Return a retryable error\n494:   3. Requeue with exponential backoff\n495: \n496: #### Scenario: Handle network timeout\n497: - **GIVEN** a Kubernetes API call times out\n498: - **WHEN** the timeout occurs\n499: - **THEN** the system SHALL treat it as retryable and requeue\n500: \n501: #### Scenario: Handle RBAC permission denied\n502: - **GIVEN** the controller lacks permissions for an operation\n503: - **WHEN** a forbidden error occurs\n504: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n505:   1. Log the error with details\n506:   2. Not retry (non-retryable)\n507:   3. Update resource status with failure\n508: \n509: #### Scenario: Handle invalid resource spec\n510: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime has an invalid spec\n511: - **WHEN** reconciliation fails validation\n512: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n513:   1. Update status with `Failed` condition\n514:   2. Record validation error in status\n515:   3. Not retry\n516: \n517: #### Scenario: Recover from panic\n518: - **GIVEN** a reconciler panics during execution\n519: - **WHEN** the panic occurs\n520: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n521:   1. Recover from the panic\n522:   2. Log the panic with stack trace\n523:   3. Update metrics\n524:   4. Continue processing other resources\n525: \n526: ---\n527: \n528: ### Requirement: Leader Election (Preparation)\n529: \n530: The system SHALL prepare for leader election to support HA deployments.\n531: \n532: #### Scenario: Configure leader election options\n533: - **GIVEN** the controller manager initializes\n534: - **WHEN** setting up the manager\n535: - **THEN** it SHALL accept leader election configuration (disabled by default in this AR)\n536: \n537: #### Scenario: Skip leader election in single-replica mode\n538: - **GIVEN** leader election is not enabled\n539: - **WHEN** the controller starts\n540: - **THEN** it SHALL start immediately without acquiring a lease\n541: \n542: #### Scenario: Leader election resource naming\n543: - **GIVEN** leader election is configured\n544: - **WHEN** acquiring the lease\n545: - **THEN** it SHALL use the lease name `agentcube-workload-manager-leader-election`\n546: \n547: ---\n548: \n549: ## File Index\n550: \n551: | Path | Purpose |\n552: |------|---------|\n553: | `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/manager.go` | Controller manager bootstrap and lifecycle |\n554: | `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/agentruntime_controller.go` | AgentRuntimeReconciler implementation |\n555: | `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/codeinterpreter_controller.go` | CodeInterpreterReconciler implementation |\n556: | `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler.go` | Base reconciler interface and utilities |\n557: | `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/finalizer.go` | Finalizer helper functions |\n558: | `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/conditions.go` | Condition management utilities |\n559: | `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/ownerref.go` | OwnerReference helper functions |\n560: | `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/metrics.go` | Prometheus metrics definitions |\n561: | `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/watch.go` | Watch event handlers and mappers |\n562: | `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/ratelimiter.go` | Rate limiter configuration |\n563: | `cmd/workload-manager/controller.go` | Controller command entry point |\n564: | `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/agentruntime_controller_test.go` | AgentRuntime reconciler tests |\n565: | `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/codeinterpreter_controller_test.go` | CodeInterpreter reconciler tests |\n566: | `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/suite_test.go` | Controller test suite setup |\n567: \n568: ---\n569: \n570: ## Dependencies\n571: \n572: | Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n573: |------------|---------|---------|\n574: | `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` | `v0.20.0+` | Controller runtime framework |\n575: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` | Local | Generated clientset and informers |\n576: | `k8s.io/client-go` | `v0.34.1` | Kubernetes client |\n577: | `k8s.io/apimachinery` | `v0.34.1` | Kubernetes API machinery |\n578: | `github.com/prometheus/client_golang` | Latest | Metrics |\n579: | `github.com/go-logr/logr` | Latest | Structured logging |\n580: \n581: ---\n582: \n583: ## API Integration\n584: \n585: | Component | Usage |\n586: |-----------|-------|\n587: | `runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime` | Resource type being reconciled |\n588: | `runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter` | Resource type being reconciled |\n589: | `client-go/informers` | Watch resource changes |\n590: | `client-go/listers` | Cached resource reads |\n591: | `controller-runtime/pkg/client` | Controller-runtime client |\n592: | `controller-runtime/pkg/reconcile` | Reconcile interface |\n593: | `controller-runtime/pkg/controller` | Controller builder |\n594: | `controller-runtime/pkg/manager` | Manager interface |\n595: \n596: ---\n597: \n598: ## Data Types\n599: \n600: ### Reconciler Configuration\n601: ```go\n602: type ReconcilerConfig struct {\n603:     MaxConcurrentReconciles int           // default: 3\n604:     RateLimiterBaseDelay    time.Duration // default: 5ms\n605:     RateLimiterMaxDelay     time.Duration // default: 1000s\n606:     MaxRetries              int           // default: 5\n607:     GracefulShutdownTimeout time.Duration // default: 30s\n608: }\n609: ```\n610: \n611: ### Reconcile Result\n612: ```go\n613: type ReconcileResult struct {\n614:     Requeue      bool\n615:     RequeueAfter time.Duration\n616:     Error        error\n617: }\n618: ```\n619: \n620: ### Finalizer Constants\n621: ```go\n622: const (\n623:     AgentRuntimeFinalizer    = \"agentruntime.agentcube.io/finalizer\"\n624:     CodeInterpreterFinalizer = \"codeinterpreter.agentcube.io/finalizer\"\n625: )\n626: ```\n627: \n628: ---\n629: \n630: ## Metrics Reference\n631: \n632: | Metric Name | Type | Labels | Description |\n633: |-------------|------|--------|-------------|\n634: | `reconcile_latency_seconds` | Histogram | controller, result | Reconciliation duration |\n635: | `reconcile_total` | Counter | controller, result | Total reconciliations |\n636: | `reconcile_queue_depth` | Gauge | controller | Current queue depth |\n637: | `reconcile_retries_total` | Counter | controller | Total retries |\n638: | `resource_status_phase` | Gauge | controller, phase | Resources by phase |\n639: \n640: ---\n641: \n642: ## Notes\n643: \n644: - The reconciler uses controller-runtime for efficient resource watching and reconciliation\n645: - Rate limiting prevents thundering herd on API server errors\n646: - Finalizers ensure cleanup before resource deletion\n647: - OwnerReferences enable Kubernetes garbage collection\n648: - Status updates use the subresource to avoid spec conflicts\n649: - The controller integrates with existing WorkloadManager HTTP service\n650: - Metrics are exposed via the same `/metrics` endpoint as the HTTP service\n651: - Leader election is prepared but not required for single-replica deployments\n652: - All controllers share a single manager and informer cache for efficiency\n\n(End of file - total 652 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-007 — K8s Reconciler 控制器\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-007  \n**Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** L  \n\nImplement the Kubernetes Reconciler Controller for the WorkloadManager using controller-runtime. The controller watches AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRs, reconciles their desired state with actual cluster state, manages sandbox lifecycle transitions, and provides event-driven reconciliation with exponential backoff, finalizers, and proper status condition management.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Controller Manager Bootstrap\n\nThe system SHALL provide a controller manager that initializes and manages reconciler controllers.\n\n#### Scenario: Start controller manager with reconcilers","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-007/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775853408837,"end":1775853408866}}}}
